## Always Remember

1. **Test your changes** - Ensure functionality works as expected
2. **Handle errors gracefully** - Don't let the application crash
3. **Follow the modular pattern** - Maintain consistency with existing code
4. **Document your changes** - Update documentation when needed
5. **Security first** - Always consider security implications
6. **Performance matters** - Write efficient code
7. **Keep it simple** - Don't over-engineer solutions

Follow these rules consistently to maintain high code quality and project stability in VX Engine. 